<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Reign1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Reign,</orth> subst. 1) exercise of royal authority, sovereignty: <bibl n="shak. wt 5.2.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 2, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.152" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 4, 152</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.4.66" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 4, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.5.198" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 5, 198</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 1, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.6.5" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 6, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.9.49" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 9, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 2, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.170" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 170</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 1, 108</bibl>. <cit><quote>during whose r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.67" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 67</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>in the r. of Bolingbroke,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.2.39" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 2, 39</bibl></cit>. Used of any dominion: <cit><quote>thus have I politicly begun my r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.191" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 1, 191</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>Timon hath done his r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.226" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 226</bibl></cit> (rhyming).<lb />2) prevalence, exercise of power: <emph>all the faults which in thy</emph> (night's) <cit><quote>r. are made,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 804" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 804</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>grim care's r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 804" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 804</bibl></cit> <emph>each</emph> (viz day and night) <cit><quote>though enemies to either's r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 28.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 28, 5</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>